    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A new version of Truffle with Solidity 0.4.11 will be released tomorrow (Monday). However, Truffle can't yet support custom compiler versions because of Solidity releasing breaking API changes on minor versions (generally considered a no no). For instance, in the last three versions (0.4.9 to 0.4.11), the API has changed twice; in order to keep Truffle from automatically breaking and preventing users from compiling at all, we have to lock down the compiler to a specific version.\r\n\r\nWe're unlikely to implement custom compiler version support until Solidity adopts better release practices, which will likely come as Solidity matures. ",
