    "body": "I'm going to close this issue as I don't see this feature being possible in the short term. Additionally, the desire for \"custom compiler versions\" generally translates to a desire for the latest version, which we try to stay on top of as much as possible. We didn't upgrade to 0.4.9 or 0.4.10 because of [a breaking change](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/1645) to the compiler output that prevented Truffle from linking library contracts. Other tools were affected as well.",
